venue.name: Dong Fang Mei Shi Fan Dian 东方美食饭店

tips.text: 辣子鸡，金针菇拌黄瓜丝，蒜泥白肉，水煮牛肉
Must try: oriental salad, drunken chicken, duck in onion pastry, fried pork chop noodle or fried rice and of course the xiao long bao!

venue.name: Song Fa Bak Kut Teh 松發肉骨茶

tips.text: The food here was great. However, the management should relook at the queuing system as there are two queues – one at each entrance.
记得： 少油，少盐，小辣，加麻。。。。

venue.name: Hong Kong Soya Sauce Chicken Rice & Noodle

formattedAddress: #02-126, Chinatown Complex Market & Food Centre (335 Smith St)

tips.text: You have to eat here at least once if you are near the china town. but beware for a long queue when lunch time. taste soooo good and cheap as well.
The buffet is really value for money. My Favourite is the brisket even though the fat content is so high. Eat with raw garlic and kimchi, chased with cold beer. It's so so good.
If you're in the mood for spice, try this! Pick from a variety of fresh veggies, meat and tofu, have them stir fry in mala spices and have it with white rice and beer. Perfect for a cold day!

venue.name: Xiu Ji Ikan Bilis Yong Tau Fu

formattedAddress: #02-87/88, Chinatown Complex Market & Food Centre (355 Smith Street)

tips.text: The ikan billis or deep fried anchovies are delicious.

venue.name: Hong Lim Market & Food Centre 芳林巴刹与熟食中心 (Hong Lim Complex Market & Food Centre)

tips.text: Best fish soup found here!

venue.name: Si Wei Mao Cai 思味冒菜

formattedAddress: 33 Mosque St (btw South Bridge Rd. & New Bridge Rd.)
location.crossStreet: btw South Bridge Rd. & New Bridge Rd.

tips.text: Their 花仁豆腐 is the best & unique.
Attentive service, delectable dishes with quality ingredients. Uni pudding is stellar
The strawberry mochi fish is sooooo nice !! In love with it
Fantastic food. $$$$$. You will not get out of there for less than SG$300 for two.
Food was only average for the pricing which will set you back at least $50++ /pax. Claimed 20% birthday discount but cashier unaware. Overall not worthy of the price.

contact.facebookName: O Batignolles Wine Bar & French Bistrot

tips.text: Great for brunch! Their butter croissant is amazingly good.
the chairs are too high and tables are too low.
紅燒肉 (Red-Cooked Pork), 紫蘇黃瓜 (Fried Cucumber)， 手撕包菜 (Stir-Fried Cabbage)，鹹蛋黃茄子(Eggplant Fingers w Salted-Egg Crust) are all splendid.
Happy hours daily till 8pm 25% off!

formattedAddress: 45 Ann Siang Hill #02-02 (Ann Siang Hill Park)

tips.text: Love the atmosphere!

BE Sanger (pulled pork, chipotle aioli - served in brioche bun): Ask 2 cut 'burger' in half- makes for a nice snack to share over cocktails. Aioli gave ea bite a mild play w d chilli & garlic flavours
Not hard to find!
Been here since I was a kid, gotta try the dai ha mai
Good quality food well priced business lunch set menu. Angus beef onglet and chips cooked perfectly, and loved the Apple crumble dessert.
Fantastic food; terrible service 😡 Served by a hovering waitress who asked "Are you done with that?" and "Can you finish that so I can clear the table?" We left within 75 minutes of being seated.
Food is totally overpriced but drinks and atmosphere at bar upstairs are great, so have dinner somewhere else and come here only for drinks.

formattedAddress: 5 Banda St, #01-52 K88 Coffee House (Sago Lane)

tips.text: Best sausage! Try Smoked Pork with Cheese!
Must try the salt baked beetroot, w burrata & truffle honey, mini Spanish breakfast, and popcorn milk chocolate mousse! The short ribs and scallops were just okay. Arrive post 930 to avoid the wait.

formattedAddress: 3 Pickering Street, #01-29 Nankin Row, China Square Central
location.address: 3 Pickering Street, #01-29 Nankin Row, China Square Central

tips.text: Fab food and really cheap.
Great bar - amazing ginger beer - get a seat in the dinning room at the bar
The spicy fragrant flavour is the best, but you need to be able to handle your szechuan peppers
The ambience is really cozy, a great place for gatherings. Best food of the night — Carne de Porco à Alentejana. It's not on the menu though.
If you've ever wondered what the right way to make your own yakiniku - this place is a must visit. The beef cuts are all fantastic, but save room for the pork jowl.

formattedAddress: 2 Teck Lim Road (Off Keong Saik Rd)

tips.text: Good value set lunch. Yummy food with even yummier desserts. Don't miss their lemon tart - One of those rare places that dares to let the tartness shines through. Love!

venue.name: 왕대박 Wang Dae Bak Korean BBQ Restaurant

tips.text: Lunch sets are great value at $10.
Best buffet in Singapore!

venue.name: Chinatown Food Street (牛車水美食街)

tips.text: Newly renovated Chinatown food street is wider, cleaner, has more stalls offering different foods including Indian food and satays, BBQ chicken and is covered by a massive glass and steel roof
order the northern stuff, obviously - good homestyle cooking. 地三鮮，醬茄子，酸菜粉絲，涼拌腐皮絲，東北拉皮 are all excellent and filling.
Try the chilli crab...

contact.facebookName: 왕대박 Wang Dae Bak Korean BBQ

tips.text: Good food with excellent service! must try the pork rib stew during lunch! not a common korean dish found in SG
Amazing, one of the best restaurants I've been to in Singapore or elsewhere...
A cold atmosphere. But good coffee & food. Wish they had a menu. It's tiring just listening to the waitress reciting it & I'm pretty sure it's tiring for them to recite it too...
Hey guys, here's our interview with Burlamacco's chef, Gabriele Piegaia...
Portion is gigantic! Love the granola and almond milk, banana, berries smoothie (vegan!) The fry up breakfast is good too and latte is really nice! Thumbs up guys!

venue.name: 老成都川菜馆 Old Chengdu Sichuan Cuisine Restaurant

tips.text: Cumin ribs, Long beans, fish in Chili
Best dining experience - has the potential to be a top 10 restaurant in the world! Chef's 8 course + dessert is full of wonderful surprises, leaving you wanting more!

formattedAddress: 14 Ann Siang Road (Ann Siang Road / Club Street)

tips.text: Great traditional Spanish tapas. Can't go wrong here
Great place for food and has a wide variety of interesting rums. :)
Love their kimchi soup and chicken . Lots of different types of dippings for your oven baked chicken!
Delicious Thai milk tea, and pleasant staff! Try the Extra Gold version if you prefer a stronger taste of tea.

formattedAddress: PARKROYAL on Pickering (3 Upper Pickering St.)

tips.text: Don't forget to try the Lime Bar. Delicious bar bites and a great club sandwich: The William.... In-or outside if the AC is too cold....
